FBIS4-16683 "drsov075_a_94009" FBIS-SOV-94-075 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Churkin Says Gorazde Fallen, Situation Out of Control Churkin Says Gorazde Fallen, Situation Out of Control LD1804201394 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 1940 GMT 18 Apr 94 LD1804201394 Moscow 2x2 Television Russian BFN [Text] The defense of Gorazde has fallen, and I believe that the situation is out of control, said Vitaliy Churkin, the Russian president's special envoy, today at Zagreb Airport before returning to Moscow. He believes that at present the most important thing for the Serbs is the lifting of international sanctions against them. All they have to do is to stop attacking Gorazde. However, the Serbs are not prepared to do it, he said.
